Union Case 1: union two trees, that their root have the same height and their number of sons <=k
perform the following: link sons from source tree to the root in the destination tree, disposing the source Root element link the root of the destination tree into the sons of the source tree notify listeners for performing a union write statistics

unionCase2(int, int, NodeManager.Root, NodeManager.Root) - Method in class mta.ads.smid.model.IUFkForest
Union Case 2: union two trees (two roots), that their root have the same height and their number of sons > k
perform the following: create a new Root element add the two trees as sons of the new root, converting them into NonRoot nodes link the two trees (NonRoot nodes) into the new root notify listeners for performing a union write statistics
